<h1 id="resolve-from">resolve-from <a href="https://travis-ci.org/sindresorhus/resolve-from"><img alt="Build Status" src="https://travis-ci.org/sindresorhus/resolve-from.svg?branch=master" /></a></h1>

<blockquote>
<p>Resolve the path of a module like <a href="http://nodejs.org/api/globals.html#globals_require_resolve"><code class="prettyprint">require.resolve()</code></a> but from a given path</p>
</blockquote>

<p>Unlike <code class="prettyprint">require.resolve()</code> it returns <code class="prettyprint">null</code> instead of throwing when the module can&rsquo;t be found.</p>

<h2 id="install">Install</h2>
<pre class="highlight plaintext"><code>$ npm install --save resolve-from
</code></pre>

<h2 id="usage">Usage</h2>
<pre class="highlight javascript"><code><span class="kr">const</span> <span class="nx">resolveFrom</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nx">require</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'resolve-from'</span><span class="p">);</span>

<span class="c1">// there's a file at `./foo/bar.js`</span>

<span class="nx">resolveFrom</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'foo'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">'./bar'</span><span class="p">);</span>
<span class="c1">//=&gt; '/Users/sindresorhus/dev/test/foo/bar.js'</span>
</code></pre>

<h2 id="api">API</h2>

<h3 id="resolvefrom-fromdir-moduleid">resolveFrom(fromDir, moduleId)</h3>

<h4 id="fromdir">fromDir</h4>

<p>Type: <code class="prettyprint">string</code></p>

<p>Directory to resolve from.</p>

<h4 id="moduleid">moduleId</h4>

<p>Type: <code class="prettyprint">string</code></p>

<p>What you would use in <code class="prettyprint">require()</code>.</p>

<h2 id="tip">Tip</h2>

<p>Create a partial using a bound function if you want to require from the same <code class="prettyprint">fromDir</code> multiple times:</p>
<pre class="highlight javascript"><code><span class="kr">const</span> <span class="nx">resolveFromFoo</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nx">resolveFrom</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="nx">bind</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="kc">null</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">'foo'</span><span class="p">);</span>

<span class="nx">resolveFromFoo</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'./bar'</span><span class="p">);</span>
<span class="nx">resolveFromFoo</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'./baz'</span><span class="p">);</span>
</code></pre>

